{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"User-controlled swap params can spend arbitrary token balances held by gateway contracts","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:373","GatewayCrossChain.sol:492","GatewayTransferNative.sol:414","GatewayTransferNative.sol:453","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574","GatewaySend.sol:199","GatewaySend.sol:245","GatewaySend.sol:366"],"claim":"The contracts decode `MixSwapParams` from attacker-controlled payloads and use `params.fromToken` / `params.fromTokenAmount` in approvals and `mixSwap` without enforcing that they match the token and net amount actually received in the current execution path.","impact":"Attackers can spend unrelated token balances already held by these contracts (fees, stranded balances, prior user funds) and route swap outputs to attacker-controlled recipients, causing direct theft.","paths":["Craft payload/swapData with `params.fromToken` set to a valuable token currently held by the contract and `params.fromTokenAmount` set to the desired drain amount.","Trigger `onCall`, `withdrawToNativeChain`, or `depositAndCall` with cheap/unrelated input.","Contract approves DODO for attacker-chosen token and `mixSwap` pulls/spends contract inventory for attacker benefit."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Refunds for non-20-byte recipients are claimable by anyone","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:607","GatewayCrossChain.sol:612","GatewayTransferNative.sol:685","GatewayTransferNative.sol:689"],"claim":"In both `claimRefund` implementations, when `walletAddress.length != 20`, `receiver` remains `msg.sender`; the caller check then trivially passes for arbitrary callers.","impact":"Refunds intended for non-EVM recipients (e.g., Bitcoin/Solana-style addresses) can be front-run and stolen by any observer.","paths":["A failed cross-chain call stores refund info with non-20-byte `walletAddress`.","Attacker observes `externalId` and calls `claimRefund(externalId)` first.","Authorization passes trivially and funds are transferred to attacker."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Bitcoin/non-EVM revert recipient is truncated to 20 bytes, misdirecting refunds","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:318","GatewayCrossChain.sol:550","GatewayTransferNative.sol:319","GatewayTransferNative.sol:631"],"claim":"`withdraw` encodes revert recipient as `bytes20(sender)`, truncating non-20-byte addresses. `onRevert` then interprets the 52-byte revert payload as an EVM address refund target.","impact":"Failed non-EVM withdrawals can refund to unintended EVM addresses (or unusable addresses), causing permanent user fund loss.","paths":["User initiates withdrawal with a non-20-byte recipient format.","Withdrawal fails and gateway calls `onRevert` with truncated 20-byte recipient bytes.","Contract refunds to that truncated EVM address instead of the intended non-EVM recipient."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"withdrawToNativeChain trusts nominal input amount and can execute underfunded withdrawals from contract reserves","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:549","GatewayTransferNative.sol:554","GatewayTransferNative.sol:555","GatewayTransferNative.sol:570","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574","GatewayTransferNative.sol:577","GatewayTransferNative.sol:599","GatewayTransferNative.sol:477"],"claim":"`withdrawToNativeChain` uses caller-supplied `amount` as the accounting source for fee/swap/withdraw flows, but does not verify actual token balance delta. The ETH sentinel path skips transfer-in entirely, and ERC20 paths only check a boolean `transferFrom` return.","impact":"Attackers can trigger withdrawals of real `decoded.targetZRC20` from contract-held inventory without providing equivalent funding, enabling direct theft of pooled assets.","paths":["Call `withdrawToNativeChain(_ETH_ADDRESS_, amount, message)` to bypass token pull, then route to valuable `targetZRC20`.","Or use a malicious/deflationary token that returns success while transferring less than `amount`.","Contract computes output from nominal `amount` and executes gateway withdrawal using existing target-token balances."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend destination onCall trusts payload amount/token data and can drain contract reserves","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:347","GatewaySend.sol:354","GatewaySend.sol:359","GatewaySend.sol:363","GatewaySend.sol:370","GatewaySend.sol:372"],"claim":"`GatewaySend.onCall` trusts `amount`, `fromToken`, and `toToken` decoded from attacker-controlled payload bytes instead of reconciling to assets delivered by gateway for that call. The function can skip funding pulls (`fromToken == ETH sentinel`) and also ignores ERC20 transfer return values.","impact":"Crafted cross-chain payloads can force ETH/ERC20 payouts from pre-existing contract balances to attacker-controlled recipients, causing direct theft.","paths":["Send cross-chain call with payload encoding inflated `amount` and attacker-chosen token mode.","Destination `onCall` computes `outputAmount` from payload values, not reconciled balances.","Contract transfers ETH/ERC20 reserves to attacker recipient."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Reentrancy in `GatewayTransferNative.claimRefund` allows repeated refund claims","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:691","GatewayTransferNative.sol:692"],"claim":"`claimRefund` performs external token transfer before deleting `refundInfos[externalId]`, enabling reentrancy on malicious refund tokens.","impact":"A malicious token can reenter and claim the same refund multiple times in one transaction, draining additional token balance held by the contract.","paths":["Create refund entry where `refundInfo.token` is a reentrant token.","Call `claimRefund(externalId)`; token transfer reenters before storage deletion.","Repeated claims execute until balance is exhausted or reentrancy stops."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Balance-based pair existence check can be dust-poisoned into swap-path DoS","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:234","GatewayCrossChain.sol:245","GatewayTransferNative.sol:235","GatewayTransferNative.sol:246","libraries/UniswapV2Library.sol:44"],"claim":"`_existsPairPool` infers pair existence by token balances at computed pair address rather than verifying deployed pair code/reserves.","impact":"Attackers can dust non-pair addresses so routing selects nonexistent direct pools, causing reserve lookups/swaps to revert and denying service for affected routes.","paths":["For a token pair without a real direct pool, send dust of both tokens to computed pair address.","`_existsPairPool` returns true and route selection chooses 2-hop direct path.","Subsequent `getReserves`/swap calls revert on non-pair target, blocking those swaps."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Public `withdraw` can be abused when residual gateway allowances remain","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:305","GatewayTransferNative.sol:319","GatewayTransferNative.sol:416","GatewayTransferNative.sol:477","GatewayTransferNative.sol:496"],"claim":"`GatewayTransferNative.withdraw` is publicly callable. Other flows approve `outputAmount + gasFee` when gas token equals output token, but gateway spends only `outputAmount`, leaving residual allowance under some conditions.","impact":"If residual approval and contract balance exist (notably after gas-fee changes), arbitrary callers may consume leftover allowance to trigger unauthorized withdrawals to attacker-chosen recipients.","paths":["A prior withdrawal path leaves nonzero residual allowance from `GatewayTransferNative` to gateway.","Attacker calls public `withdraw` with attacker-controlled recipient bytes and amount that fits remaining allowance conditions.","Gateway pulls contract tokens via leftover allowance and emits withdrawal to attacker destination."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Empty `swapDataZ` path allows cross-asset withdrawals without performing conversion","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:369","GatewayCrossChain.sol:492","GatewayCrossChain.sol:495","GatewayCrossChain.sol:517","GatewayTransferNative.sol:449","GatewayTransferNative.sol:414","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574","GatewayTransferNative.sol:577","GatewayTransferNative.sol:599"],"claim":"When `swapDataZ` is empty, `_doMixSwap` returns the input `amount` directly. Callers can still set arbitrary `decoded.targetZRC20`, and withdrawal/payout logic proceeds as if a real conversion occurred.","impact":"Attackers can provide one asset but withdraw/receive a different, more valuable token from contract-held reserves, causing direct reserve theft.","paths":["Send message/call with `targetZRC20 != input zrc20` and empty `swapDataZ`.","`_doMixSwap` returns nominal input amount without any token conversion proof.","Contract executes withdraw/transfer in `targetZRC20` using its own inventory."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend source flow does not bind bridged asset to swap output asset","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:245","GatewaySend.sol:257","GatewaySend.sol:266","GatewaySend.sol:170","GatewaySend.sol:186"],"claim":"`depositAndCall(fromToken,...)` computes a numeric `outputAmount` from `_doMixSwap`, then deposits whichever `asset` the caller supplied, without verifying that this asset was actually produced/received from the swap.","impact":"If the contract holds balances of another token/ETH, attackers can swap one asset but bridge out a different asset from pooled reserves.","paths":["Call `depositAndCall(fromToken, amount, swapData, ..., asset, ...)` with swap output token different from `asset`.","Obtain nonzero `outputAmount` (or force it via crafted swap data).","Contract deposits `outputAmount` of attacker-chosen `asset` to gateway, consuming contract reserves."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"GatewayTransferNative refund records are overwriteable for the same externalId","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:642","GatewayTransferNative.sol:648","GatewayTransferNative.sol:664","GatewayTransferNative.sol:670"],"claim":"`onRevert`/`onAbort` in `GatewayTransferNative` write `refundInfos[externalId]` without checking whether an entry already exists.","impact":"If duplicate/colliding callbacks occur for the same `externalId`, earlier refund metadata can be replaced, leading to refund loss, misdirection, or permanent unclaimability for the original claimant.","paths":["First callback stores refund info for `externalId = X`.","Second callback with same `X` stores different wallet/token/amount and overwrites prior data.","Original user can no longer claim intended refund entry."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"AccountEncoder.decompressAccounts builds invalid memory layout for `Account[]`","locations":["libraries/AccountEncoder.sol:28","libraries/AccountEncoder.sol:33","libraries/AccountEncoder.sol:48","GatewayCrossChain.sol:425","GatewayCrossChain.sol:454","GatewayTransferNative.sol:505","GatewayTransferNative.sol:534"],"claim":"`decompressAccounts` stores pointers in array slots where static `Account` structs are expected inline, so later ABI encoding reads corrupted struct fields.","impact":"Solana-targeted payloads can be malformed and fail downstream decoding/calls, causing persistent route-level DoS/refund churn for affected transf