ves/deposits full `amount` to gateway.","Gateway pull succeeds using contract-held inventory to cover the shortfall, transferring value to attacker-controlled cross-chain flow."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend destination finalizes success even when ERC20 payout transfer fails softly","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:372","GatewaySend.sol:385"],"claim":"`onCall` executes `IERC20(toToken).transfer(...)` without checking the returned boolean and then returns success to the gateway.","impact":"If a token returns `false` (instead of reverting), cross-chain delivery is marked successful while recipient payment never happens, causing silent non-delivery and potential fund lockup in the contract.","paths":["Process destination message where payout token's `transfer` returns `false`.","`onCall` does not revert and still returns success.","No revert/refund path is triggered, while recipient remains unpaid."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend ETH payout uses `.transfer` and can DoS smart-contract recipients","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:370"],"claim":"ETH delivery uses Solidity `.transfer`, forwarding only 2300 gas to the recipient.","impact":"Many contract wallets/proxies cannot receive ETH under 2300 gas; affected cross-chain deliveries deterministically revert, reducing liveness for those recipients.","paths":["Set destination recipient to a contract with non-trivial `receive`/`fallback` logic.","`onCall` executes `payable(recipient).transfer(outputAmount)`.","Transfer reverts and delivery path fails for that recipient class."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend revert handler lacks native-asset refund path and can strand reverted ETH","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:393","GatewaySend.sol:396"],"claim":"`onRevert` always calls ERC20-style `Tran